   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-1-a" mid="113" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="111"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>It's full of mystery.<BR>It seems like I get it yet I don't get it?!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-1-b" mid="115" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="114"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>Come to think of it, there is a legend that the Knight King subdued the Desert Dragon.<BR>It's not recorded in the history books because he never admitted it himself....<BR>Could this have something to do with that incident?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-2" mid="131" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="116"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>And this female knight called Aisha may have something to do with the Desert Dragon raid as well.<BR>I may be jumping to conclusions… but I'm really curious.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="118"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR><FONT color=#387206>{user_nick}</FONT>, if you come across other information at Memoria... won't you bring them to me?<BR>I will keep it as a secret to other people.<BR><BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>* New records can be found at Memoria Part III.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-a" mid="121" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="119"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>You're here! Shhh! Keep quiet and don't attract my uncle or General Douglas's attention.<BR>I don't like creating trouble.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Cassius delightedly picks up the records you've brought)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-b" mid="123" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="122"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>Huh? What?! Don't tell me Aisha was the <FONT color=#a82424>Desert Dragon</FONT>! No way.<BR>I thought she was just a young girl?<BR>
And the female knight who helped in establishing our Cassius Kingdom is also recorded in history books.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-c" mid="135" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="133"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>It is said that the female knight disappeared right after the Knight King took the throne.<BR>I suspected her existence was only a legend since she wasn't mentioned in history anymore.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-e" mid="137" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Say you don't know)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-d" mid="138" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Say that whether you are a dragon or a human doesn't matter in true friendship)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-e" mid="139" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Keep quiet)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="136"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>But if she was the Desert Dragon...<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Cassius looks around and lowers his voice)</FONT><BR>Why did a dragon help Knight King Cassius?!<BR>
Dragons are evil monsters, aren't they?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-e" mid="146" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="145"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>
Hmm… Maybe you're right.<BR>
What kind of species you are or how old you are doesn't matter if you share true feelings.<BR>
For example, I believe that a king and a <FONT color=#387206>{user_class}</FONT> can be good friends.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-f" mid="142" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="140"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>Anyway, I think I understand why this wasn't recorded.<BR>
The country might have fell into chaos if it was announced that a dragon helped to establish the nation.<BR>But it was too much of that general to initiate a raid against her. She was still their saviour and a comrade.<BR>
Don't you think so?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n040_king_casius-3-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n040_king_casius-3-g" mid="148" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="147"><![CDATA[<html>$King Cassius$<BR>Do such choices have to be made for the welfare of the kingdom?<BR>Hmm... I really don't know. Am I too young to understand this?<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Cassius keeps pondering over this)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
